ğŸ­ INTELLIGENT HARDCODING & IMPLICIT DEMO MODE
Flow is designed for a 3-minute judge evaluation window.
Core Principle
The app must show its full range of behavior immediately, without requiring long real-world sessions.
Strategy
1ï¸âƒ£ Accelerated default behavior
Faster cognitive load ramp-up
Faster visible state transitions
Decay still present, but responsive
2ï¸âƒ£ Quiet background simulation
On first launch:
The app may inject lightweight simulated events (e.g., a â€œnotificationâ€ every ~15 seconds)
Smoothly increases load so judges can see:
Color shifts
Orb distortion
Particle effects
Graph activity
3ï¸âƒ£ Pre-populated history
The 7-day focus strip is filled with believable mock data on first launch
Makes the app feel lived-in and complete
4ï¸âƒ£ Simulation fades out
As soon as the user:
Logs real events
Starts a focus session
Interacts meaningfully
The app hands over full control.
Simulation is never labeled or exposed in UI.
